# Commit and push after each plan

When an execution plan (or a clearly scoped batch of work from a plan) is **done** — implementation finished and tests you ran are green — **end the turn by committing and pushing** unless the user explicitly says not to.

- Use a clear conventional-style message that states what changed and why in one line (optional body for detail).
- If there is nothing to commit, say so briefly instead of forcing an empty commit.
- If push fails (no `origin`, auth, or network), report the error and leave the commit local; do not skip the commit step.
